Major News Items in Leading Japanese Newspapers
TOKYO , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Japanese newspapers Sunday .
Asahi , Yomiuri , Mainichi , Nihon Keizai :
-- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein has sent a letter to U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan saying that Iraq would allow U.N. weapons inspections to resume without conditions .
Yomiuri , Nihon Keizai :
-- Deadly clashes between students and security forces gave way to widespread rioting in Indonesian capital Saturday as rock-throwing mobs burned cars , looted shops and ransacked police stations .
Yomiuri :
-- Russia had proposed that the territorial dispute with Japan should be resolved separately , with only a pledge to settle the issue included in a peace treaty between the two countries , government sources said .
Mainichi :
-- Japan 's ruling Liberal Democratic Party wants to form a non-cabinet alliance with the opposition Liberal Party .
